  {
    "section_type": "discussion",
    "type": "minutes_chunk",
    "document_type": "minutes",
    "document_subtype": "officer",
    "source_file": "September 30 _ Officer Meeting.txt",
    "role": "N/A",
    "person": "N/A",
    "content": "* VP External: Bid for ESSCO PM 2027\n* Ashna: uOttawa has to bid for both ESSCO and CFES conferences every so often. VP Services of ESSCO/CFES says we are not due to bid until next year. I talked to them and think it is good to bid for the above which is good for us. We could wait, but don’t want to be left with a larger conference that is harder to do, especially if I am no longer around. SDES is larger (National), leading me to choose ESSCO (Ontario) PM.\n* Hayley: I worry that…\n* Cyrus: Is there money involved?\n* Ashna: There is a budget required in the bid but a portion is covered by the ESSCO/CFES and some would be applied for from EEF.\n* Cyrus: Sponsors? C&R? VEMS?\n* Ashna: We can chat about logistics later. ESSCO PM is an ESSCO Conference out of 2 coming up. We can bid for ESSCO PM at FYIC or CALE. I think CALE is better as there isn’t much time to prepare for FYIC.\n* Aiden: Third time is a charm!\n* Eric: Gonna ask bod? Just need to get votes as it involves society finances.\n* Ashna: Okay. For the bid I have to prepare a template for the organizing committee. If you are interested in joining let me know.\n* VP External: Carleton hockey fundraiser\n* Hayley: Carleton reached out and they wanted to do something like they did in the past with Telfer.\n* Ashna: Me and Alper chatted but we don’t have much info. Emailed (organizer?) and wants to set up a meeting. I wanted to know logistics like dates etc. Want to see if this is something we want to do???\n* Hayley: If this is a fundraiser then we shouldn't incur cost.\n* Ashna: We have past costs and shou\n* Hayley: IMO, if only 300 estimated to be made, seems like a lot of work unless logistics are already done.\n* Eric: If it is a fundraising event, involve Zoe.\n* Cyrus: Is there interest in hockey?\n* Alper: Yes, we have people reaching out.\n* Hayley: Use money for jerseys to keep each year. Pay to watch not pay to play.\n* Ashna: Worried because I am being told I would need to pay for SDES. Alper and I will have a convo. Leaving Zoe out as this is not a fundraiser for external organizations.\n* Cyrus: Option to purchase and keep jersey?\n* Hayley: Keep them year round, ESS branded\n* VPFA: October Monster: Covies4Monster?? Thoughts??\n* Cyrus: Switch it up for October from Math. Similar to WWWC??\n* Hayley: Improve WWWC and add Monster to it as well.\n* Conall: Halloween costume for Monster.\n* Hayley: For 3 weeks do WWWC. Last week and leading to DUSTED, do costumes.\n* VP Academic: W&C email simplifications?\n* Nick: There are 4 can we cut that down?\n* Hayley: Are they not linked?\n* Nick: No.\n* Hayley: Let’s just link them.\n* Adi: I will make sure all emails that have secondaries will be linked\n* VPFA: Does anyone know if Luke has been cutting locks? (Who knows?)\n* Cyrus: We have sold 99. One person bought winter??\n* Nobody Knows…\n* VP Social : Weekly Wednesday at Nostalgica??\n* Magno: Somebody contacted about missing a midweek gathering. Weekly Wednesday’s at Nostalgica???\n* Hayley: The only question was “Let me know if you have a couple students to help with the soft launch” which was weird. I don’t know what it has to do with us and how it benefits us.\n* Adi: Signup form?\n* Cyrus: No\n* Hayley: It is a mess. The guy is weird. (paraphrased)\n* NOT FROM BAR DIRECTLY\n* Hayley: Respond with no, but if it goes well reach out and we can promote. Generally weak sell from them.\n* Magno: Everyone knows about karaoke at FNS.",
    "meeting_date": "2025-09-30",
    "meeting_date_display": "September 30th 2025 7pm"
  },
